[30;1m354 | [0m[35m    # now we need to convert from two matrices to one kxk conv kernel and one[0m
[30;1m355 | [0m[35m    # 1x1 conv kernel. Here's why the 2nd has to be a 1x1: if it were instead[0m
[30;1m356 | [0m[35m    # k'xk' for some k' > 1, we would either be doing k'^2 as much work[0m
[30;1m357 | [0m[35m    # for fixed embedding size at each pixel, or we'd be need to have the[0m
[30;1m358 | [0m[35m    # intermediate embeddings be 1/k'^2 as large. In the latter case, we'd[0m
[30;1m359 | [0m[35m    # lose a lot of representational capacity. Also, the first op has to match[0m
[30;1m360 | [0m[35m    # the kernel size of the original conv or the shapes don't work out.[0m

[30;1m119 | [0m[35m                and the associated value is a list of values of that metric. The remaining[0m
